Details

5 linear ft. (1 carton, 3 oversize volumes)

Contains speeches and newspapers of the 18th and 19th century; correspondence, clippings, and scrapbooks

Teacher, lawyer, Lieutenant Governor, U.S. Representative from Idaho Springs, Colorado

Open to qualified researchers

Warren Armstrong Haggott Collection (MSS #282), Colorado Historical Society, Denver, Colorado

No part of this collection may be photocopied, reproduced or in any other way published without the expressed written permission of the Curator of Books and Manuscripts, Colorado Historical Society

Finding aid available
